@Velo_816: Sorry, but I'm not sure. The version in this torrent is 3.2.8.13.

@SilentKiller411: You need to copy the RCT3plus.exe in this torrent and paste into the RollerCoaster Tycoon 3 install directory. When it asks you to overwrite the old RCT3plus.exe, say yes.

The default install directory for RollerCoaster Tycoon 3 should be "C:\Program Files (x86)\Atari\RollerCoaster Tycoon 3"; so find your "RollerCoaster Tycoon 3" folder and paste the cracked RCT3plus.exe into there and choose to replace the old one when you're asked.

@Nupjook - I'm using Windows 7 and it worked fine for me. Are you using MagicDisc to mount the ISO? If not, try it with MagicDisc. Also make sure you downloaded the torrent completely, that way you don't have only part of the ISO file.

Another possible problem could be that you're trying to use the ISO while seeding the ISO. The solution is to keep seeding the ISO you downloaded and copy and paste that ISO into a different folder and mount the new copied ISO.

So here's what you should try. Start by making sure you're using MagicDisc. Now unmount the ISO, copy and paste the ISO you downloaded in this torrent to a different folder, mount the new copied ISO to a virtual drive with MagicDisc, and try running it. Again make sure the ISO was completely downloaded. If that doesn't work, restart your computer and try mounting it again.
